tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  89,1,"Allah may He be glorified takes an oath on the dawn."
  89,2,"And He takes an oath on the first ten nights of Dhul-á¸¤ijjah."
  89,3,"He also takes an oath on the odd and even of things."
  89,8,"The likes of which Allah never created in the cities."
  89,11,"All these people transgressed the limit in tyranny and oppression; each of them transgressed it in his land."
  89,12,"They caused an abundance of corruption due to spreading disbelief and sins."
  89,18,"Neither do any of you encourage the other in feeding the poor person who cannot find anything to consume."
  89,21,"These actions are not befitting of you. Remember when the earth will be moved vigorously and shaken."